pageContext.claim: “Hispanic-American and Asian-American unemployment have also reached their lowest rates in the history of our country.”
pageContext.analysis: The Asian-American statistic has been around for less than 20 years, and it has increased to 3 percent in August since it reach a low of 2 percent in May. It was as low as 2.6 percent under Obama. The Hispanic-American statistic has only been collected since the 1970s. It reached a low of 4.5 percent in July but the day after the speech, the August figure showed an increase to 4.7 percent
